,p_name=>'HELP_GLOSSARY'
,p_message_text=>wwv_flow_string.join(wwv_flow_t_varchar2(
'<div class="textRegion"><a name="GLOSSARY"></a>',
'<h2>Glossary</h2>',
'<dl>',
'<dt>Census</dt>',
'<dd>A sample that includes the entire population.</dd>',
'<dt>Population</dt>',
'<dd>A specific group of people that you want to learn about through survey research.</dd>',
'<dt>Questionnaire</dt>',
'<dd>A questionnaire is the set of questions being asked during a survey.</dd>',
'<dt>Respondent</dt>',
'<dd>A person from the sample. Each respondent is invited to participate in the survey but they may or may not actually submit the questionnaire.</dd>',
'<dt>Response</dt>',
'<dd>A completed questionnaire submitted by a respondent.</dd>',
'<dt>Sample</dt>',
'<dd>A subset of the population.</dd>',
'<dt>Sample Size</dt>',
'<dd>The number of people in the sample. The size of the sample is important for making',
'valid generalizations about the population. The sample size depends on the size of the population,',
'the desired precision (how close the measured results are to the actual value) and',
'the confidence level (how confident you are that the selected sample is actually representative of the population)',
'Consult a statistics text book for how to calculate the sample size.</dd>',
'<dt>Sample, Non-probability</dt>',
'<dd>A sample of the population chosen by non-random methods including using human judgment.',
'A non-probability sample does not ensure the sample is representative of the population and',
'cannot be used to make generalizations about the population.</dd>',
'<dt>Sample, Probability (or random)</dt>',
'<dd>A sample of the population chosen at random. Each person in the population has the same chance',
'of being included in the sample. This ensures that the sample is representative of the population and',
'that generalizations can be made about the population from the sample.</dd>',
'<dt>Sample, Self-selected</dt>',
'<dd>A survey where anyone in the population can choose to participate in the survey.',
'This is a non-probability sample. The sample can be biased and for this reason it is',
'not valid to generalize to the whole population. For example dissatisfied',
'customers may be more likely to choose to participate in a product satisfaction survey.</dd>',
'<dt>Survey</dt>',
'<dd>A survey contains a questionnaire as well as other attributes that govern the process of conducting a survey.</dd>',
'</dl>',
'</div>'))
);
