,p_help_text=>wwv_flow_string.join(wwv_flow_t_varchar2(
'',
'<h2>About this Application</h2>',
'<p>Survey Builder manages the process of conducting survey research. The purpose of a survey',
'is to support decision making by characterizing knowledge, beliefs, attitudes, and behaviors of a specific',
'group of people (the population) through the study of a subset of them. When done correctly a ',
'survey allows generalization from the population subset to the whole population. Survey Builder',
'supports a collaborative team approach to survey research.</p>',
'',
'<p>The primary tool of a survey is the questionnaire.',
'Survey Builder provides a simple user interface for creating great looking web based questionnaires.',
'There are a number of options to control the style and format of the questionnaires.',
'The questionnaires work on a wide range of browsers on mobile, tablet, and desktop platforms.',
'Survey builder can distribute the questionnaire by sending a URL to the questionnaire via email. It',
'can also send reminder and thank you emails.',
'You can also download the list of URLs to manually distribute them for example using a separate email system.</p>',
'<p>Survey Builder supports random sample and self selected survey types.',
'The type controls the way the survey is conducted:</p>',
'<ul>',
'<li>Self selected - Anyone can choose to participate in the survey. A single URL is used to access',
'the questionnaire. Typically a link to this URL is added to a web page and visitors of that page can ',
'choose to participate by clicking the link. Adding the link to your web site is outside the scope of Survey Builder.',
'A unique code is created when a response is received. There is no way to ',
'guard against a single person or automated script submitting multiple responses.</li>',
'<li>Random sample - The survey is targeted at a specific set of respondents.',
'Typically the respondents are randomly selected from the whole population ',
'but this type can also be used for a census (the whole population) or even a non-probability sample.',
'A URL with a unique code is sent to the selected people. The unique code ensures that a person',
'responds at most once.</li>',
'</ul>',
'<p>A survey should be anonymous. Even when Survey Builder is used to distribute the questionnaire',
'via email it never shows the email address associated with the respondents.',
'The point is not to learn about specific individuals but a group as a whole.',
'In the rare case where you want to associate a response with an individual',
'(perhaps for the purpose of follow up questions) you should include a question',
'that asks the respondent for contact information such as name, email address or phone number. ',
'Ideally this identifying information is optional.</p>',
'',
'<p>The survey life cycle consists of a number of states. Initially the survey is in the design state.',
'Only in the design state can the questionnaire be edited. When ready for testing, ',
'the survey transitions to the test state. Feedback from test subjects is used to update the',
'questionnaire. You can iterate between design and test as many times as it takes to get the',
'questions just right. When ready to distribute to the respondents the survey transitions to',
'the active state. After a specific amount of time or the desired percentage of responses has',
'been received the survey transitions to the complete state. For meaningful analysis it ',
'is important that the questionnaire is immutable once the survey is active and complete.</p>',
''))
